               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0175QMA">ʾAbrǝqo Māryām / QMA</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1850" notAfter="1900">The time of King Mǝnǝlik II (r.
                        1889-1913) is mentioned in Additio 5 (s. <locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>b);
                        this suggests that the main text has been written before this
                        period.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>ḫaläqa Ḫāyla Māryām, according to Additio 3
                     (s. 8vb, ls. 1-9). His name is also mentioned in
                     the heading of each Gospel, together with the name of his wife, ʾAmata Māryām
                     (s. also Additio 3, and the heading of Gospels of Mark, Luke and John). Names
                     of other individuals, mentioned as the children of the donor, are in Additio 3:
                     Gabra Madḫǝn, Gabra Māryām, Gabra Śǝllāse, Walatta Mikāʾel, Gabra ʾAragāwi,
                     Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer, Gabra Mikāʾel, Gabra ʾIyasus, ʾAmata Gärima, Gabra Takla
                     Hāymānot.</provenance></history>
